2008 Empire State Games/ Hudson Valley Region/ Qua
description: This is qualifying road race for Empire State Games for the Hudson Valley Region Cycling Team.  For open men, 1-10 qualify for the team with 5 alternates.  For open women, 1-3 qualify for the team with 2 alternates. The race for Open men begins at 7:00 AM and Open women will immediately follow.  The 2008 Empire State Games will be held in Binghamton, New York from Wednesday July 23 to Sunday July 27, 2008.
course: The course is 1.8 mile loop with two inclines at FDR State Park, Yorktown, N.Y.  The road surface is good.
registration:
Online: www.BikeReg.com
Mail: pre-registration entries with standard release forms to:  Clarence Ballard  64 Ellwood Ave. Mt Vernon, N.Y. 10552-3404 / Phone: (914)667-3144
Race day: Parking lot #2, FDR State Park Yorktown, N.Y. at 6:15 AM
notes:
To compete in the Empire State Games Regional trial the following rules apply:
1  Competitors may only race in the region in which they reside or where they are attending school at the time of the qualifying competition.  Proof of attendance or school card must be presented at registration.
2  No past or present professionals will be eligible to compete.
3  All participants must have an USA Cycling license, an approved SNELL/ANSI helmet and abide by all USA Cycling rules.
Those who qualify must compete in all events.  Team members will travel to the games by bus and all expenses will be paid.
directions:
Directions by car
From Westchester: Bronx River Parkway north to Taconic State Parkway north to Exit for Rte. 202/35 east. Proceed 1/2 mile to park entrance on the right.
From North: Taconic State Parkway south to Exit for Rte. 202/35 east.  Proceed 1/2 mile to park entrance on the right.
From West: Interstate 84 east to Exit #16(Taconic State Parkway south).  Follow directions from North.
Note: No truck, bus or commercial vehicle on Bronx River Pkwy, Hutchinson River Pkwy & Saw Mill River Pkwy.

title: CRCA ITT Club Championship
description: 11.5 mile TT for all categories. Event is CRCA Club Championship. Only CRCA members are eligible for Club Championship but all riders are eligible for all prizes in all categories.
course: 2.2 mile flat course. Roads are rough in spots and it can be very windy.
directions:
The closest highway is the Belt Parkway.

•If you\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'re coming from the Brooklyn Queens Expressway, go east on the Belt.
•If you\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'re coming from the Verrazano Narrows Bridge, go east on the Belt.

Take the Belt Parkway to exit 11, aka Flatbush Ave South. You\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'re on Flatbush for less than half a mile. Last left before toll takes you into the park.

Make first left turn, and travel 1/2 mile to first right turn. Turn right and go half way up runway. Make the first left turn and stay on your left side. Park against the wood chips.

Getting to Floyd Bennett Field by Bike:

For Manhattanites, cross the Brooklyn Bridge. Go left on Tillary. two blocks and take the right on Flatbush Avenue. Take Flatbush Avenue all the way there. You\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'ll climb through Park Slope, go around Grand Army Plaza so the Museum is on your left and the park on your right. And keep on going.

Brooklynites have to get themselves to Flatbush and go.
